\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{example}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

 be a set.
 An object 
\begin_inset Formula $(E,p)\in\mathbf{Set}/S$
\end_inset

 can be pictured like this: 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
end{example}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


